<div data-type="commentary" id="fs-id1165040740648" data-element-type="hint"><div data-type="title">Hint</div>
<p id="fs-id1165042005368">Use the double-angle formula for cosine.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="example" id="fs-id1170572111814">
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170572550138">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170572550140"><div data-type="title">Proving a Trigonometric Identity</div>
<p id="fs-id1170572550142">Prove the trigonometric identity <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>tan</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>sec</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>tan</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>sec</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1170572136968">
<p id="fs-id1170572224130">We start with the identity</p>
<div data-type="equation" id="fs-id1170572167191" class="unnumbered" data-label=""><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
<p id="fs-id1170572140245">Dividing both sides of this equation by <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> we obtain</p>
<div data-type="equation" id="fs-id1170572481849" class="unnumbered" data-label=""><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
<p id="fs-id1170572114646">Since <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mtext>/</mtext><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>tan</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mtext>/</mtext><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>tan</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>sec</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>sec</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> we conclude that</p>
<div data-type="equation" id="fs-id1170572481963" class="unnumbered" data-label=""><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>tan</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>sec</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>tan</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>sec</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="note" id="fs-id1170572239833" class="checkpoint">
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170572171308">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170572171310">
<p id="fs-id1170572226907">Prove the trigonometric identity <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cot</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>csc</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cot</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>csc</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="commentary" id="fs-id1165041809085" data-element-type="hint"><div data-type="title">Hint</div>
<p id="fs-id1165041809092">Divide both sides of the identity <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>cos</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> by <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
