<p id="fs-id1170572452031">For the following exercises, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is a point on the unit circle. a. Find the (exact) missing coordinate value of each point and b. find the values of the six trigonometric functions for the angle <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>&#952;</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> with a terminal side that passes through point <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>P</mi><mo>.</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Rationalize denominators.</p>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170572452051">
