<p id="fs-id1170572147850">For the following exercises, each graph is of the form <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace width="0.1em"/><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>B</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace width="0.1em"/><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>B</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> or <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace width="0.1em"/><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>B</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace width="0.1em"/><mtext>cos</mtext><mspace width="0.1em"/><mi>B</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> where <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Write the equation of the graph.</p>
